graph { flow: south; }

# README architecture — deployment side-channel.
#
# The newtlab engine puts SONiC VMs on the network (creates QEMU processes,
# wires socket links) and exits. specs feed the newtron engine at load time.
# Neither path runs during normal operation — these are setup/lifecycle
# concerns.

[ specs ]       --> [ newt-server\n(newtron engine) ]
[ newtlab CLI ] --> { label: deploy, wire; } [ SONiC VM ]
